  <discussion>Physcomitrium hookeri lacks the toothed leaves and small annular cells that characterize other members of the genus.  Although its distal leaf margins are often uneven from slightly bulging cells, they are never clearly toothed, and its revoluble annulus is composed of large, inflated cells.</discussion>
